				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					Thanks Taipo,<br />
 <br />
I may just &quot;cherry pick&quot; some of the code from the .htaccess hardening as I don't have a lot of attack attempts on my stores.<br />
 <br />
I have read that a good way to stop access attempts to the admin section is to have a dedicated IP address for your ISP connection and to ban all but this IP address via .htaccess.<br />
 <br />
However, I (like a lot of people Im sure) connect via a dynamic IP address which changes with each connection to the internet.<br />
 <br />
However, the first two numbers of my IP address are always the same - Is there a way to write this into the .htaccess file to only allow IPs that commence with the two numbers to connect to admin (using wildcards?)<br />
 <br />
I know that this would only block IPs from outside my region / country? but I think that would be a useful additional security addition - as most of the attempted attacks are, in my case, non-UK in their origin.<br />
 <br />
Many Thanks
					
					<br />
					
				</div>
				
				
